SIMPLE: postmark
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Postmark
<hw>Post"mark`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The mark, or stamp,
of a post office on a letter, giving the place and date of mailing or of
arrival.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postmark</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Postmark
<hw>Post"mark`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Postmarked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Postmarking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To mark with a post-office
stamp; <as>as, to <ex>postmark</ex> a letter or parcel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postmaster</ent>⟦br⟧
